# ETL Architecture Invariants

- Keep ETL self-contained: no runtime dependency on other microservices.
- PostgreSQL is the only external runtime dependency.
- Preserve parity between CLI (`licitia-etl`) and FastAPI operations when adding capabilities.
- Maintain clear separation of concerns:
  - `etl/cli.py`: CLI orchestration
  - `etl/api.py`: REST transport layer
  - `etl/ingest_l0.py`: ingestion and registry logic
  - `etl/scheduler.py`: scheduling and run lifecycle
  - `schemas/`: SQL DDL and migrations
- Add new data sources through explicit registry/configuration, not hidden side effects.
- Prefer idempotent ingestion and safe re-runs over one-shot scripts.
- Changes that alter architecture contracts must update `README.md` and `CHANGELOG.md`.
